<subSubSection id="C34E48C5FF8E4021FF6021B1FC4ADB4C" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEB1B4EFF8E4021FF6021B1FC4ADB4C" blockId="8.[151,1437,325,1396]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8E4021FF6021B1FE9ADB30" bold="true" box="[199,315,1262,1288]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described based on a 
<typeStatus id="54EFA5ECFF8E4021FD4921B1FCF1DB30" box="[750,848,1262,1288]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">holotype</typeStatus>
male from 
<collectingRegion id="4990D5ACFF8E4021FC6921B1FBDBDB30" box="[974,1146,1262,1288]" country="Russia" name="Amur" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">Amur Province</collectingRegion>
as a new species assigned to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5460CDFF8E4021FEEB204CFE1BDB14" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[332,442,1299,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Lissempis">
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8E4021FEEB204CFE1BDB14" box="[332,442,1299,1324]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">Lissempis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but later was left unassigned (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC566BFFF8E4021FCB2204DFC6CDB15" author="Shamshev, I. V." box="[789,973,1298,1325]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" pagination="3 - 183" refId="ref6950" refString="Shamshev, I. V. (2016) An annotated checklist of empidoid flies (Diptera: Empidoidea, except Dolichopodidae) of Russia. Proceedings of the Russian Entomological Society, 87, 3 - 183. https: // doi. org / 10.47640 / 1605 - 7678 _ 2016 _ 87 _ 5" type="journal article" year="2016">Shamshev 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5460CDFF8E4021FC47204CFB3FDB14" authorityName="Shamshev" authorityYear="1998" box="[992,1182,1299,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amurensis">
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8E4021FC47204CFB3FDB14" box="[992,1182,1299,1324]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">Empis amurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5460CDFF8E4021FF732068FE39DB68" authority="Saigusa, 2022" authorityName="Saigusa" authorityYear="2022" box="[212,408,1334,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicoloriventris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8E4021FF732068FE39DB68" box="[212,408,1334,1360]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">E. bicoloriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8E4021FE382069FE58DB68" bold="true" box="[415,505,1334,1360]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2137A27FF8E4021FE382069FE58DB68" box="[415,505,1334,1360]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the entirely blackish male abdomen. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C5460CDFF8E4021FB632068FA9DDB68" authority="Saigusa, 2022" authorityName="Saigusa" authorityYear="2022" box="[1220,1340,1334,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oshimai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8E4021FB632068FA9DDB68" box="[1220,1340,1334,1360]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">E. oshimai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B920C75CFF8E4021FAE42069FA3DDB68" bold="true" box="[1347,1436,1334,1360]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2137A27FF8E4021FAE42069FA3DDB68" box="[1347,1436,1334,1360]" pageId="8" pageNumber="113" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from the Ryukyus. Differences between them are stated in the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
